Man jumped into Brush Creek in Kansas City after being stopped by police for a hit-and-run in the early hours of Friday morning . 
  The 38-year-old driver smashed his 2007 Infinity into a bridge and jumped into the water . 
  He spent 10-15 minutes swimming in the water and threatened police with a log . 
  Police officers and firefighters followed him into the creek and fished him out . 
  He was taken to a hospital with a broken leg . 
 